        \              }\n\
        \         }\n\
        \  "]
  availability_zone : string_ option;
      [@ocaml.doc
        "The Availability Zone (AZ) where the DB instance will be created.\n\n\
        \ Default: A random, system-chosen Availability Zone.\n\
        \ \n\
        \  Constraints:\n\
        \  \n\
        \   {ul\n\
        \         {-  You can't specify the [AvailabilityZone] parameter if the DB instance is a \
         Multi-AZ deployment.\n\
        \             \n\
        \              }\n\
        \         }\n\
        \   Example: [us-east-1a] \n\
        \   "]
  db_subnet_group_name : string_ option;
      [@ocaml.doc
        "The DB subnet group name to use for the new instance.\n\n\
        \ Constraints:\n\
        \ \n\
        \  {ul\n\
        \        {-  If supplied, must match the name of an existing DB subnet group.\n\
        \            \n\
        \             }\n\
        \        }\n\
        \   Example: [mydbsubnetgroup] \n\
        \   "]
  multi_a_z : boolean_optional option;
      [@ocaml.doc
        "Secifies whether the DB instance is a Multi-AZ deployment.\n\n\
        \ This setting doesn't apply to RDS Custom.\n\
        \ \n\
        \  Constraints:\n\
        \  \n\
        \   {ul\n\
        \         {-  You can't specify the [AvailabilityZone] parameter if the DB instance is a \
         Multi-AZ deployment.\n\
        \             \n\
        \              }\n\
        \         }\n\
        \  "]
  publicly_accessible : boolean_optional option;
      [@ocaml.doc
        "Specifies whether the DB instance is publicly accessible.\n\n\
        \ When the DB cluster is publicly accessible, its Domain Name System (DNS) endpoint \
         resolves to the private IP address from within the DB cluster's virtual private cloud \
         (VPC). It resolves to the public IP address from outside of the DB cluster's VPC. Access \
         to the DB cluster is ultimately controlled by the security group it uses. That public \
         access isn't permitted if the security group assigned to the DB cluster doesn't permit it.\n\
        \ \n\
        \  When the DB instance isn't publicly accessible, it is an internal DB instance with a \
         DNS name that resolves to a private IP address.\n\
        \  \n\
        \   For more information, see [CreateDBInstance].\n\
        \   "]
  auto_minor_version_upgrade : boolean_optional option;
      [@ocaml.doc
        "Specifies whether minor version upgrades are applied automatically to the DB instance \
         during the maintenance window.\n\n\
        \ This setting doesn't apply to RDS Custom.\n\
        \ \n\
        \  For more information about automatic minor version upgrades, see \
         {{:https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonRDS/latest/UserGuide/USER_UpgradeDBInstance.Upgrading.html#USER_UpgradeDBInstance.Upgrading.AutoMinorVersionUpgrades}Automatically \
         upgrading the minor engine version}.\n\
        \  "]
  license_model : string_ option;
      [@ocaml.doc
        "The license model information for the restored DB instance.\n\n\
        \  License models for RDS for Db2 require additional configuration. The bring your own \
         license (BYOL) model requires a custom parameter group and an Amazon Web Services License \
         Manager self-managed license. The Db2 license through Amazon Web Services Marketplace \
         model requires an Amazon Web Services Marketplace subscription. For more information, see \
         {{:https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonRDS/latest/UserGuide/db2-licensing.html}Amazon RDS \
         for Db2 licensing options} in the {i Amazon RDS User Guide}.\n\
        \  \n\
        \    This setting doesn't apply to Amazon Aurora or RDS Custom DB instances.\n\
        \    \n\
        \     Valid Values:\n\
        \     \n\
        \      {ul\n\
        \            {-  RDS for Db2 - [bring-your-own-license | marketplace-license] \n\
        \                \n\
        \                 }\n\
        \            {-  RDS for MariaDB - [general-public-license] \n\
        \                \n\
        \                 }\n\
        \            {-  RDS for Microsoft SQL Server - [license-included | bring-your-own-media] \n\
        \                \n\
        \                 }\n\
        \            {-  RDS for MySQL - [general-public-license] \n\
        \                \n\
        \                 }\n\
        \            {-  RDS for Oracle - [bring-your-own-license | license-included] \n\
        \                \n\
        \                 }\n\
        \            {-  RDS for PostgreSQL - [postgresql-license] \n\
        \                \n\
        \                 }\n\
        \            }\n\
        \   Default: Same as the source.\n\
        \   "]
  db_name : string_ option;
      [@ocaml.doc
        "The database name for the restored DB instance.\n\n\
        \ This parameter doesn't apply to the following DB instances:\n\
        \ \n\
        \  {ul\n\
        \        {-  RDS Custom\n\
        \            \n\
        \             }\n\
        \        {-  RDS for Db2\n\
        \            \n\
        \             }\n\
        \        {-  RDS for MariaDB\n\
        \            \n\
        \             }\n\
        \        {-  RDS for MySQL\n\
        \            \n\
        \             }\n\
        \        }\n\
        \  "]
  engine : string_ option;
      [@ocaml.doc
        "The database engine to use for the new instance.\n\n\
        \ This setting doesn't apply to RDS Custom.\n\
        \ \n\
        \  Valid Values:\n\
        \  \n\
        \   {ul\n\
        \         {-   [db2-ae] \n\
        \             \n\
        \              }\n\
        \         {-   [db2-ce] \n\
        \             \n\
        \              }\n\
        \         {-   [db2-se] \n\
        \             \n\
        \              }\n\
        \         {-   [mariadb] \n\
        \             \n\
        \              }\n\
        \         {-   [mysql] \n\
        \             \n\
        \              }\n\
        \         {-   [oracle-ee] \n\
        \             \n\
        \              }\n\
        \         {-   [oracle-ee-cdb] \n\
        \             \n\
        \              }\n\
        \         {-   [oracle-se2] \n\
        \             \n\
        \              }\n\
        \         {-   [oracle-se2-cdb] \n\
        \             \n\
        \              }\n\
        \         {-   [postgres] \n\
        \             \n\
        \              }\n\
        \         {-   [sqlserver-ee] \n\
        \             \n\
        \              }\n\
        \         {-   [sqlserver-se] \n\
        \             \n\
        \              }\n\
        \         {-   [sqlserver-ex] \n\
        \             \n\
        \              }\n\
        \         {-   [sqlserver-web] \n\
