         Using SSL/TLS to encrypt a connection to a DB cluster} in the {i Amazon Aurora User \
         Guide}.\n\
        \  "]
  additional_storage_volumes : additional_storage_volumes_list option;
      [@ocaml.doc
        "A list of additional storage volumes to create for the DB instance. You can create up to \
         three additional storage volumes using the names [rdsdbdata2], [rdsdbdata3], and \
         [rdsdbdata4]. Additional storage volumes are supported for RDS for Oracle and RDS for SQL \
         Server DB instances only.\n"]
  tag_specifications : tag_specification_list option;
      [@ocaml.doc
        "Tags to assign to resources associated with the DB instance.\n\n\
        \ Valid Values: \n\
        \ \n\
        \  {ul\n\
        \        {-   [auto-backup] - The DB instance's automated backup.\n\
        \            \n\
        \             }\n\
        \        }\n\
        \  "]
}
